oop review rule is already established process, not an open planning gap.\n- Keep the rule-level safety result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that containment-first version safety is established process, not an open planning gap.\n- Keep the rule-level isolation result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that mailbox state stays isolated from legacy board/tab metadata, so rollback remains straightforward.\n- Keep the rule-level opt-in result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that team-mode surfaces remain additive and secondary, not replacements for existing single-thread flows.\n- Keep the rule-level non-regression result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that current mailbox work has stayed non-destructive across thread lifecycle, board interaction, auto-continue, and loop-control surfaces.\n- Keep the rule-layer cleanup result fixed: for the current mailbox scope, rule-level process and safety debt is effectively closed; remaining unresolved work is execution hardening plus later delivery hygiene.\n- Keep the analysis-convergence result fixed: further analysis-only repo edits are no longer justified unless a new regression or containment need appears.\n- Keep the post-convergence result fixed: repeated analysis after convergence has not surfaced any new regression, so the remaining critical-path work is still the Task 6 resolver slice.\n- Keep the post-convergence discipline fixed: analysis-only mailbox passes should stop mutating task-plan or active-plan scope unless a new regression, drift signal, or containment need appears.\n- Keep the forced-analysis discipline fixed: if a caller keeps requiring another analysis-only mailbox pass without new evidence, limit repo edits to a minimal handoff refresh and preserve the same execution target.\n- Keep the repeated-analysis refresh discipline fixed: when such a minimal refresh is unavoidable, only restate the same Task 6 resolver handoff instead of reopening task-plan scope or adding 